"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-01-olympic-golf-commentators-apologise-rory-mcilroys-sweary-outburst-21344220\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Commentators were forced to apologise after Rory McIlroy used 'some colourful language' during the opening round of golf at theParis2024Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 44, \"end\": 56, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rory McIlroy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rory_McIlroy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The golf finally got underway on Thursday morning at Le Golf National course with the likes of Great Britain'sTommy Fleetwoodand Matt Fitzpatrick swinging for gold.\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 276, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Fitzpatrick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Fitzpatrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Fitzpatrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Fitzpatrick\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIlroy, who isrepresenting Ireland and not Team GB, finished the first round three-under-par, with some work to do to catch leader Hideki Matsuyama ofJapanwho carded eight-under.\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9982374420198862, \"rank\": 0.0016998679520298034, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 357, \"end\": 364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9898331002023256, \"rank\": 0.01026958411840185, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hideki Matsuyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hideki_Matsuyama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 35-year-old also kept commentators on their toes after a sweary outburst on the 17th hole.\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As he tee shot veered to the right, McIlroy appeared to shout 's**t', and though the audible wasn't entirely clear, the Discovery commentators immediately issued an apology to viewers.\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'A colourful character, some colourful language,' one said before chipped in: 'Apologies for anything that came through the mic.'\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterlosing the US Open in heartbreaking fashionandcrashing out of The Open in embarrassing fashion, McIlroy is hoping some Olympic gold can remedy his woeful form.\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Solid start.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A bit up-and-down, which is to be expected,' he said in the clubhouse.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'A little disappointing with the three-putt at the last.\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Something to build upon.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With so many events going on spread all across the city, for people to venture out here and to watch us play, it was a really cool atmosphere to play in.\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'[I was] not [expecting] this.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought the weekend, it might get a few more people.\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought the first couple days might be a little bit quieter but it was awesome.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I'd say maybe 25 per cent were more of a casual crowd or sports crowd rather than a golf crowd.\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's nice to play in front of that because it provides a bit more energy.\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'There is a few more flags and there is a bit more, I do not know what the word is, like nationalism.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we were all really well-supported out there.\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was great to see.'\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1909, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Fleetwood finished the day on four-under-par, with Fitzpatrick far behind on two-over.\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1922, \"end\": 1931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.5965616135919234, \"rank\": 0.6759657112681223, \"text\": \"Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fleetwood_Town_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latter was forced to wait to finish his round after play was suspended twice because of a risk of lightning strikes at the course.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro S